  "texts": [
    "The readability scores did not significantly correlate with the participants' ratings of the quality of the texts.",
    "While readability is certainly an important component of quality, it is possible that participants focused their attention more on the logic of the argument rather than on the rhetoric.",
    "We purposefully kept the userperceived quality ratings abstract.",
    "It would have been possible to further divide quality into aspects of readability, such as grammar and spelling.",
    "However, this would have potentially excluded the more abstract \"tone\" of the text."
  ],
